<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.edit_check> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "EditCheck evaluates a proposed edit's content against the active repo-scoped advisory rules (\"detect\" blocks) that apply to the file, in the caller's resolved domain. It is WARNING-ONLY: it never blocks, never modifies code, and returns warnings naming the rule a bad-shape edit would violate (e.g. replacing dispenser.Errf with fmt.Errorf in a Caddy Caddyfile unmarshaler). Domain scoping is identical to Briefing/Impact: a multi-domain graph with no domain fails closed; cross-domain rules never apply. See golang/server/scope.go. — rpc EditCheck(EditCheckRequest) returns (EditCheckResponse)" .
