<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.metadata> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Contract> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.metadata> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Metadata returns coverage and freshness signals about the graph itself — not about any specific file. Agents call this at session start so they can tell whether an EMPTY briefing means \"no rules apply here\" (graph is well-covered) vs \"this area is unannotated\" (graph coverage is thin in this domain).  Cheap: counts are computed live via SPARQL but the queries are bounded and small. Safe to call once per session or per task. — rpc Metadata(MetadataRequest) returns (MetadataResponse)" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.metadata> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AwarenessGraph.Metadata" .
