<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.preflight> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Contract> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.preflight> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Preflight is the agent's pre-edit decision-support call. Given a task and optional file list, it returns a single risk_class the agent can branch on, plus required_actions, forbidden_fixes, tests_to_run, and files_to_read assembled from anchored graph facts (never invented).  Reuses Briefing's matching engine; adds risk classification, coverage discipline, and action-oriented response shape on top. EMPTY does NOT become LOW_RISK unless coverage explicitly says coverage is sufficient — if the graph doesn't know the area, the response is UNKNOWN_IMPACT and the agent is told to proceed carefully.  Store unavailable degrades to PREFLIGHT_STATUS_DEGRADED with UNKNOWN_IMPACT and blind_spots=\"awareness_store_unavailable\" rather than hard-failing. Only returns codes.Unavailable if the handler cannot construct any response at all. — rpc Preflight(PreflightRequest) returns (PreflightResponse)" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.preflight> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AwarenessGraph.Preflight" .
