<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.propose> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Contract> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.propose> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Propose submits a typed feedback entry (failure_mode, invariant, required_test, forbidden_fix, or contract_unknown) to the awareness corpus's review queue. It is the agent write path: an agent that learned something durable proposes it here.  The entry is validated with the SAME contract-first rules as `awg propose` and written as a candidate under docs/awareness/candidates/proposals/ — it is NOT a live graph node and does NOT trigger a rebuild. Promotion into the canonical corpus stays a human/CI-gated step, so the served graph never silently mutates durable truth (preserving the CLI-not-durable-mutation contract; the RPC only queues a proposal). Requires the server to be configured with a candidates directory; returns Unavailable otherwise. — rpc Propose(ProposeRequest) returns (ProposeResponse)" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.propose> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AwarenessGraph.Propose" .
