<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.reference_sites> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Contract> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.reference_sites> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "ReferenceSites returns, for each requested code-symbol id, the set of OTHER code symbols that reference it (inbound aw:references edges from ingested SCIP occurrences). This is the completeness primitive: given the symbols a change touches, it answers \"N sites share this reference; which ones did the diff miss?\". Directed and complete — it reads inbound edges straight from the store, so a target with many OUTGOING references does not crowd out its referencing sites (as a bidirectional related-walk would). External targets (stdlib/third-party, id \"external:<name>\") have no in-repo definition and are ignored. Cheap: one inbound describe per id. — rpc ReferenceSites(ReferenceSitesRequest) returns (ReferenceSitesResponse)" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#contract/contract.awareness_graph.reference_sites> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AwarenessGraph.ReferenceSites" .
