<https://globular.io/awareness#decision/decision.awareness_mutation_enforcement.desired> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Decision> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#decision/decision.awareness_mutation_enforcement.desired> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Awareness-source mutations remain non-observed and non-authoritative by themselves, but may become conditionally behavior-supported when the enforcement path is explicit, bounded, and verified." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#decision/decision.awareness_mutation_enforcement.desired> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Closure currently distinguishes observed behavior from architectural intent but does not yet recognize deterministic enforcement for canonical awareness-source mutations. This leaves legitimate architecture-sensitive changes blocked even when the affected source is governed by closed validation and graph compilation." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#decision/decision.awareness_mutation_enforcement.desired> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Exact mutations to governed awareness sources should be eligible for conditional behavioral support when Sensei can prove a deterministic validation and graph-build enforcement path for that source." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#decision/decision.awareness_mutation_enforcement.desired> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Awareness-source mutation should gain deterministic enforcement recognition" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#decision/decision.awareness_mutation_enforcement.desired> <https://globular.io/awareness#affects> <https://globular.io/awareness#invariant/awareness.authored_knowledge_sources_are_governable_repository_files> .
