<https://globular.io/awareness#decision/decision.awareness_mutation_enforcement.intended> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Decision> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#decision/decision.awareness_mutation_enforcement.intended> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Canonical awareness-source mutations should be evaluated through explicit enforcement plans derived from deterministic importer, validation, and graph-build steps rather than by treating the YAML declaration itself as observed behavior." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#decision/decision.awareness_mutation_enforcement.intended> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Conditional behavioral support depends on explicit enforcement receipts; it does not establish architectural correctness or permit task-local knowledge to become canonical truth." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#decision/decision.awareness_mutation_enforcement.intended> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The enforcement path must remain revision-bound, task-bound, and policy-bound so that closure and admission agree on what verification is required before mutation may be attempted." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#decision/decision.awareness_mutation_enforcement.intended> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Awareness-source mutation enforcement is derived from deterministic validation and graph build" .
