<https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenFix/forbidden_fix.sensei.map_an_absent_optional_count_to_zero> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/forbidden_fixes.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenFix/forbidden_fix.sensei.re_derive_graph_authority_or_severity_in_the_webview> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ForbiddenFix> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenFix/forbidden_fix.sensei.re_derive_graph_authority_or_severity_in_the_webview> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The CP3 control panel must read authority (observed/current/integrity) and severity from the control snapshot verbatim. Re-deriving them client-side (the pre-CP3 graphAuthority.ts/dashboard.js cockpit derivation) reintroduces the drift the migration removed." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenFix/forbidden_fix.sensei.re_derive_graph_authority_or_severity_in_the_webview> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Re-derive graph authority or severity in the webview" .
