<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.authoring_gate_must_match_seed_generator_strictness> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Guardrail> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.authoring_gate_must_match_seed_generator_strictness> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The awareness authoring gate (awg validate) must be at least as strict as the seed generator (yaml2nt -validate-refs) for dangling cite-without-define references (Test and ForbiddenFix anchors). In the 2026-06 episode, contracts passed awg validate but cited 22 undefined test anchors and 1 undefined forbidden_fix; yaml2nt rejected them and the seed rebuild aborted, jamming the consuming repo's embeddata-freshness gate AFTER the contracts had already merged. Do not rely on awg validate alone to prove a contract is seed-safe: a reference is \"defined\" only when it has an aw:authoredIn anchor (a required_tests.yaml / forbidden_fixes entry), not merely when the underlying Go test exists. Fix: awg validate should share yaml2nt's dangling-ref check, or run yaml2nt -validate-refs as part of the authoring gate." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.authoring_gate_must_match_seed_generator_strictness> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "learning.authoring_gate_must_match_seed_generator_strictness" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.authoring_gate_must_match_seed_generator_strictness> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/learning_rules.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.check_principle_coverage_after_classification> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Guardrail> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.check_principle_coverage_after_classification> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "After classifying an error under a meta-principle, the agent must check whether the principle's enforcement section already covers this specific case. If not, one of three actions is needed:\n  1. A new forbidden_fix entry (if the error was a known-bad repair pattern)\n  2. A new required_test entry (if the error is regressionable)\n  3. An updated enforcement description (if the scope was too narrow)\nThis ensures principles grow in precision, not just in instance count." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.check_principle_coverage_after_classification> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "learning.check_principle_coverage_after_classification" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.check_principle_coverage_after_classification> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/learning_rules.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.classify_error_against_principles> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Guardrail> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.classify_error_against_principles> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "When an AI agent documents an error (failure_mode, incident_pattern, or finding), it must attempt to classify the error against the existing generative meta-principles (invariant:meta.*). The classification step asks: \"which principle was violated?\" If one fits, the error entry must include a related_invariants link to the meta-principle. This connects specific errors to the class of bugs they belong to, so future briefings surface not just \"this specific thing broke\" but \"this is an instance of a known architectural weakness.\"" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.classify_error_against_principles> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "learning.classify_error_against_principles" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.classify_error_against_principles> <https://globular.io/awareness#affects> <https://globular.io/awareness#invariant/meta.absence_scope_must_be_explicit> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.classify_error_against_principles> <https://globular.io/awareness#affects> <https://globular.io/awareness#invariant/meta.authority_must_express_uncertainty> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.classify_error_against_principles> <https://globular.io/awareness#affects> <https://globular.io/awareness#invariant/meta.fallback_must_degrade_semantics> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.classify_error_against_principles> <https://globular.io/awareness#affects> <https://globular.io/awareness#invariant/meta.half_done_must_not_look_done> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.classify_error_against_principles> <https://globular.io/awareness#affects> <https://globular.io/awareness#invariant/meta.identity_computation_must_be_invariant> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.classify_error_against_principles> <https://globular.io/awareness#affects> <https://globular.io/awareness#invariant/meta.silence_is_not_valid_for_unexpected> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.classify_error_against_principles> <https://globular.io/awareness#affects> <https://globular.io/awareness#invariant/meta.storage_is_not_semantic_authority> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.classify_error_against_principles> <https://globular.io/awareness#affects> <https://globular.io/awareness#invariant/meta.write_creates_completion_obligation> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.classify_error_against_principles> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/learning_rules.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.error_to_principle_workflow> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Guardrail> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.error_to_principle_workflow> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The complete workflow for an AI agent processing an error:\n\n  1. DOCUMENT — write the error as failure_mode or incident_pattern with\n     evidence, symptoms, root cause, and resolution.\n\n  2. CLASSIFY — run the error against meta-principles (invariant:meta.*).\n     Ask: \"which principle was violated?\" If one fits, add\n     related_invariants: [meta.<id>]. If none fits, flag as unclassifiable.\n\n  3. CHECK COVERAGE — does the principle's enforcement already cover this\n     case? If not, propose a new forbidden_fix, required_test, or\n     enforcement update.\n\n  4. SEARCH FOR SIBLINGS — use the principle as a lens to search for\n     similar violations in code that hasn't broken yet. The principle\n     predicts where the same class of bug is hiding. Report findings\n     even if no fix is made immediately.\n\n  5. REPORT — end the error analysis with:\n     - Error classification: <meta-principle ID> or UNCLASSIFIABLE\n     - Coverage gap: <what enforcement was missing>\n     - Sibling search: <N violations found / N clean>\n     - Principle strength: <total instances under this principle>" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.error_to_principle_workflow> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "learning.error_to_principle_workflow" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.error_to_principle_workflow> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/learning_rules.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.escalate_unclassifiable_errors> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Guardrail> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.escalate_unclassifiable_errors> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "If an error does not fit any existing meta-principle, the agent must flag it explicitly: \"this error does not match any known generative principle — potential new principle needed.\" This is the signal for a human-AI session to zoom out from the specific error and look for the generating function. Unclassifiable errors are where the next architectural insight is hiding. The agent should NOT force-fit the error into an existing principle — a bad classification is worse than no classification." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.escalate_unclassifiable_errors> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "learning.escalate_unclassifiable_errors" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.escalate_unclassifiable_errors> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/learning_rules.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.failure_modes_need_evidence> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Guardrail> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.failure_modes_need_evidence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Failure modes proposed from an incident must reference the source incident, include at least one symptom, a root cause, and an architecture fix. Failure modes without evidence links are rejected during validation." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.failure_modes_need_evidence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "learning.failure_modes_need_evidence" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.failure_modes_need_evidence> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/learning_rules.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.must_be_reviewable> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Guardrail> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.must_be_reviewable> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "AI-generated awareness must be written as proposal YAML in docs/awareness/proposals/, not directly promoted to approved awareness files. Every proposal must be validated and approved before it becomes architecture law." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.must_be_reviewable> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "learning.must_be_reviewable" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.must_be_reviewable> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/learning_rules.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.no_silent_invariant_creation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Guardrail> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.no_silent_invariant_creation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "New critical invariants require explicit human approval before becoming active. AI may propose invariants, but the promotion step is always gated by a validated proposal and a deliberate operator action." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.no_silent_invariant_creation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "learning.no_silent_invariant_creation" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.no_silent_invariant_creation> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/learning_rules.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.no_weakening_existing_laws> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Guardrail> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.no_weakening_existing_laws> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "AI proposals must not delete or weaken existing critical invariants. A proposal that lowers severity, removes forbidden fixes, or removes required tests from an existing critical invariant is automatically rejected by the validator." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.no_weakening_existing_laws> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "learning.no_weakening_existing_laws" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.no_weakening_existing_laws> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/learning_rules.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.principle_strength_grows_with_instances> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Guardrail> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.principle_strength_grows_with_instances> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "When multiple errors are classified under the same meta-principle, the principle becomes more concrete and more trustworthy. The agent should note when a principle has accumulated new instances since the last session. A principle with 5+ classified instances across different subsystems is load-bearing architecture — it should be treated with the same weight as a hard rule." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.principle_strength_grows_with_instances> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "learning.principle_strength_grows_with_instances" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.principle_strength_grows_with_instances> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/learning_rules.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.required_tests_for_critical_invariant> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Guardrail> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.required_tests_for_critical_invariant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Critical invariants must include at least one required test or an explicit TODO test entry documenting what test must be written. Invariants without tests are rejected during validation." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.required_tests_for_critical_invariant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "learning.required_tests_for_critical_invariant" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.required_tests_for_critical_invariant> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/learning_rules.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.seed_follows_producer_not_predeclare> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Guardrail> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.seed_follows_producer_not_predeclare> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "For an awareness triple OWNED by a consuming repo (e.g. a sourceFile -> implements -> invariant edge generated from that repo's contracts), the consuming repo is the PRODUCER of truth and the embedded seed FOLLOWS its default branch — the seed is rebuilt from the producer's default branch AFTER the producer lands (post-merge rebuild). Predeclaring the triple in the seed first FAILS, because the seed-freshness gate validates the seed against the producer's default branch, which cannot generate the triple until the producer merges (the 2026-06 AG #125 deadlock). Producer lands first; seed follows. Allowed-temporary-red policy: a producer PR may merge with its embeddata-freshness gate red ONLY when ALL hold — the failure is embeddata-freshness only, caused solely by owned-triple lag between the PR and the seed, all functional checks (build/tests/lint) green, and a mandatory immediate seed rebuild follows the merge. This is \"merge with a known post-merge seed-refresh obligation,\" not \"merge red because we don't care.\"" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.seed_follows_producer_not_predeclare> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "learning.seed_follows_producer_not_predeclare" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#guardrail/learning.seed_follows_producer_not_predeclare> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/learning_rules.yaml" .
