<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/implementation_pattern.collect_impact_scope_resolver> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Impact/briefing resolves a domain scope once; downstream loaders filter by the resolved scope and untagged nodes default to the home domain, so foreign rules never apply to the wrong repo." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/implementation_pattern.collect_impact_scope_resolver> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Resolving scope once and filtering downstream keeps each repo's briefing free of foreign rules and gives agents valid architectural context." .
