<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: code-review\nSource path: skills/engineering/code-review/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: code-review" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Review the changes since a fixed point (commit, branch, tag, or merge-base) along two axes — Standards (does the code follow this repo's documented coding standards?) and Spec (does the code match what the originating issue/PRD asked for?). Runs both reviews i" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_code_review.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Always a judgement call. Each smell is a labelled heuristic (\"possible Feature Envy\"), never a hard violation — and, like any standard here, skip anything tooling already enforces." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Both axes run as parallel sub-agents so they don't pollute each other's context, then this skill aggregates their findings." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "End with a one-line summary: total findings per axis, and the worst issue within each axis (if any). Don't pick a single winner across axes — that's the reranking the separation exists to prevent." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Present the two reports under ## Standards and ## Spec headings, verbatim or lightly cleaned. Do not merge or rerank findings — the two axes are deliberately separate (see Why two axes)." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "A PRD/spec file under docs/, specs/, or .scratch/ matching the branch name or feature." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "A path the user passed as an argument." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Anything in the repo that documents how code should be written, such as CODING_STANDARDS.md or CONTRIBUTING.md." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Before going further, confirm the fixed point resolves (git rev-parse <fixed-point>) and the diff is non-empty. A bad ref or empty diff should fail here — not inside two parallel sub-agents." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Each smell reads *what it is* → *how to fix*; match it against the diff:" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "If nothing is found, ask the user where the spec is. If they say there isn't one, the Spec sub-agent will skip and report \"no spec available\"." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Issue references in the commit messages (#123, Closes #45, GitLab !67, etc.) — fetch via the workflow in docs/agents/issue-tracker.md." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "On top of whatever the repo documents, the Standards axis always carries the smell baseline below — a fixed set of Fowler code smells (Refactoring, ch.3) that applies even when a repo documents nothing. Two rules bind it:" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Spec — does the code faithfully implement the originating issue / PRD / spec?" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Standards — does the code conform to this repo's documented coding standards?" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "The issue tracker should have been provided to you — run /setup-matt-pocock-skills if docs/agents/issue-tracker.md is missing." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "The repo overrides. A documented repo standard always wins; where it endorses something the baseline would flag, suppress the smell." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.code_review> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: codebase-design\nSource path: skills/engineering/codebase-design/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: codebase-design" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Shared vocabulary for designing deep modules. Use when the user wants to design or improve a module's interface, find deepening opportunities, decide where a seam goes, make code more testable or AI-navigable, or when another skill needs the deep-module vocabu" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Use when designing a workflow, interface, or promotion path for implementation pattern candidates and governance rules." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_codebase_design.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Accept dependencies, don't create them." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Deepening a cluster given its dependencies — see DEEPENING.md: dependency categories, seam discipline, and replace-don't-layer testing." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "One adapter means a hypothetical seam. Two adapters means a real one. Don't introduce a seam unless something actually varies across it." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Return results, don't produce side effects." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Use these terms exactly — don't substitute \"component,\" \"service,\" \"API,\" or \"boundary.\" Consistent language is the whole point." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "A Module has exactly one Interface (the surface it presents to callers and tests)." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "A Seam is where a Module's Interface lives." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Can I hide more complexity inside?" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Can I reduce the number of methods?" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Can I simplify the parameters?" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Depth is a property of a Module, measured against its Interface." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Depth is a property of the interface, not the implementation. A deep module can be internally composed of small, mockable, swappable parts — they just aren't part of the interface. A module can have internal seams (private to its implementation, used by its ow" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Interface — everything a caller must know to use the module correctly: the type signature, but also invariants, ordering constraints, error modes, required configuration, and performance characteristics. Avoid: API, signature (too narrow — they refer only to t" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Locality — what maintainers get from depth: change, bugs, knowledge, and verification concentrate in one place rather than spreading across callers. Fix once, fixed everywhere." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Small surface area. Fewer methods = fewer tests needed. Fewer params = simpler test setup." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "The deletion test. Imagine deleting the module. If complexity vanishes, it was a pass-through. If complexity reappears across N callers, it was earning its keep." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "The interface is the test surface. Callers and tests cross the same seam. If you want to test *past* the interface, the module is probably the wrong shape." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.codebase_design> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: diagnosing-bugs\nSource path: skills/engineering/diagnosing-bugs/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: diagnosing-bugs" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "A discipline for hard bugs. Skip phases only when explicitly justified." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Diagnosis loop for hard bugs and performance regressions. Use when the user says \"diagnose\"/\"debug this\", or reports something broken/throwing/failing/slow." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_diagnosing_bugs.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Do not proceed until you have reproduced and minimised." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Never \"log everything and grep\"." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Show the ranked list to the user before testing. They often have domain knowledge that re-ranks instantly (\"we just deployed a change to #3\"), or know hypotheses they've already ruled out. Cheap checkpoint, big time saver. Don't block on it — proceed with your" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Stop and say so explicitly. List what you tried. Ask the user for: (a) access to whatever environment reproduces it, (b) a captured artifact (HAR file, log dump, core dump, screen recording with timestamps), or (c) permission to add temporary production instru" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "The loop produces the failure mode the user described — not a different failure that happens to be nearby. Wrong bug = wrong fix." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "This is the skill. Everything else is mechanical. If you have a tight pass/fail signal for the bug — one that goes red on this bug — you will find the cause; bisection, hypothesis-testing, and instrumentation all just consume it. If you don't have one, no amou" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "CLI invocation with a fixture input, diffing stdout against a known-good snapshot." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Curl / HTTP script against a running dev server." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Done when every remaining element is load-bearing — removing any one of them makes the loop go green." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Failing test at whatever seam reaches the bug — unit, integration, e2e." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Headless browser script (Playwright / Puppeteer) — drives the UI, asserts on DOM/console/network." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "If you catch yourself reading code to build a theory before this command exists, stop — jumping straight to a hypothesis is the exact failure this skill prevents. No red-capable command, no Phase 2." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Phase 1 is done when the loop is tight and red-capable: you can name one command — a script path, a test invocation, a curl — that you have already run at least once (paste the invocation and its output), and that is:" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Property / fuzz loop. If the bug is \"sometimes wrong output\", run 1000 random inputs and look for the failure mode." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Red-capable — it drives the actual bug code path and asserts the user's exact symptom, so it can go red on this bug and green once fixed. Not \"runs without erroring\" — it must be able to catch this specific bug." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Replay a captured trace. Save a real network request / payload / event log to disk; replay it through the code path in isolation." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Throwaway harness. Spin up a minimal subset of the system (one service, mocked deps) that exercises the bug code path with a single function call." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "When exploring the codebase, read CONTEXT.md (if it exists) to get a clear mental model of the relevant modules, and check ADRs in the area you're touching." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.diagnosing_bugs> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: domain-modeling\nSource path: skills/engineering/domain-modeling/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: domain-modeling" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Build and sharpen a project's domain model. Use when the user wants to pin down domain terminology or a ubiquitous language, record an architectural decision, or when another skill needs to maintain the domain model." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_domain_modeling.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "CONTEXT.md should be totally devoid of implementation details. Do not treat CONTEXT.md as a spec, a scratch pad, or a repository for implementation decisions. It is a glossary and nothing else." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "When a term is resolved, update CONTEXT.md right there. Don't batch these up — capture them as they happen. Use the format in CONTEXT-FORMAT.md." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Actively build and sharpen the project's domain model as you design. This is the *active* discipline — challenging terms, inventing edge-case scenarios, and writing the glossary and decisions down the moment they crystallise. (Merely *reading* CONTEXT.md for v" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Hard to reverse — the cost of changing your mind later is meaningful" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Surprising without context — a future reader will wonder \"why did they do it this way?\"" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "The result of a real trade-off — there were genuine alternatives and you picked one for specific reasons" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.domain_modeling> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.implement> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.implement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: implement\nSource path: skills/engineering/implement/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.implement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: implement" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.implement> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Implement a piece of work based on a spec or set of tickets." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.implement> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.implement> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_implement.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.implement> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Run typechecking regularly, single test files regularly, and the full test suite once at the end." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.implement> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.implement> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: improve-codebase-architecture\nSource path: skills/engineering/improve-codebase-architecture/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: improve-codebase-architecture" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Scan a codebase for deepening opportunities, present them as a visual HTML report, then grill through whichever one you pick." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_improve_codebase_architecture.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "ADR conflicts: if a candidate contradicts an existing ADR, only surface it when the friction is real enough to warrant revisiting the ADR. Mark it clearly in the card (e.g. a warning callout: \"contradicts ADR-0007 — but worth reopening because…\"). Don't list e" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Do NOT propose interfaces yet. After the file is written, ask the user: \"Which of these would you like to explore?\"" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Then use the Agent tool with subagent_type=Explore to walk the codebase. Don't follow rigid heuristics — explore organically and note where you experience friction:" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "User rejects the candidate with a load-bearing reason? Offer an ADR, framed as: \"Want me to record this as an ADR so future architecture reviews don't re-suggest it?\" Only offer when the reason would actually be needed by a future explorer to avoid re-suggesti" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Files — which files/modules are involved" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Problem — why the current architecture is causing friction" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Read the project's domain glossary (CONTEXT.md) and any ADRs in the area you're touching first." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Run the /codebase-design skill for the architecture vocabulary (module, interface, depth, seam, adapter, leverage, locality) and its principles (the deletion test, \"the interface is the test surface\", \"one adapter = hypothetical seam, two = real\"). Use these t" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Solution — plain English description of what would change" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "The domain language in CONTEXT.md gives names to good seams; ADRs in docs/adr/ record decisions this command should not re-litigate." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Where are modules shallow — interface nearly as complex as the implementation?" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Where do tightly-coupled modules leak across their seams?" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Where does understanding one concept require bouncing between many small modules?" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Where have pure functions been extracted just for testability, but the real bugs hide in how they're called (no locality)?" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Which parts of the codebase are untested, or hard to test through their current interface?" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Write a self-contained HTML file to the OS temp directory so nothing lands in the repo. Resolve the temp dir from $TMPDIR, falling back to /tmp (or %TEMP% on Windows), and write to <tmpdir>/architecture-review-<timestamp>.html so each run gets a fresh file. Op" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.improve_codebase_architecture> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: prototype\nSource path: skills/engineering/prototype/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: prototype" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Build a throwaway prototype to answer a design question. Use when the user wants to sanity-check whether a state model or logic feels right, or explore what a UI should look like." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Use prototype when building a throwaway validator or generated candidate experiment for skill ingestion." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Use when prototyping a validator, state model, workflow, or implementation option to answer a design question before committing production code." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_prototype.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Delete or absorb when done. When the prototype has answered its question, either delete it or fold the validated decision into the real code — don't leave it rotting in the repo." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "No persistence by default. State lives in memory. Persistence is the thing the prototype is checking, not something it should depend on. If the question explicitly involves a database, hit a scratch DB or a local file with a clear \"PROTOTYPE — wipe me\" name." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "One command to run. Whatever the project's existing task runner supports — pnpm <name>, python <path>, bun <path>, etc. The user must be able to start it without thinking." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Skip the polish. No tests, no error handling beyond what makes the prototype runnable, no abstractions. The point is to learn something fast and then delete it." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Surface the state. After every action (logic) or on every variant switch (UI), print or render the full relevant state so the user can see what changed." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Throwaway from day one, and clearly marked as such. Locate the prototype code close to where it will actually be used (next to the module or page it's prototyping for) so context is obvious — but name it so a casual reader can see it's a prototype, not product" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "\"Does this logic / state model feel right?\" → LOGIC.md. Build a tiny interactive terminal app that pushes the state machine through cases that are hard to reason about on paper." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "\"What should this look like?\" → UI.md. Generate several radically different UI variations on a single route, switchable via a URL search param and a floating bottom bar." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.prototype> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: research\nSource path: skills/engineering/research/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: research" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Investigate a question against high-trust primary sources and capture the findings as a Markdown file in the repo. Use when the user wants a topic researched, docs or API facts gathered, or reading legwork delegated to a background agent." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Use when researching repository behavior, importer rules, candidate directory skip behavior, or implementation facts from primary sources." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_research.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Investigate the question against primary sources — official docs, source code, specs, first-party APIs — not a secondary write-up of them. Follow every claim back to the source that owns it." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Save it where the repo already keeps such notes; match the existing convention, and if there is none, put it somewhere sensible and say where." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Spin up a background agent to do the research, so you keep working while it reads." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Write the findings to a single Markdown file, citing each claim's source." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.research> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: resolving-merge-conflicts\nSource path: skills/engineering/resolving-merge-conflicts/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: resolving-merge-conflicts" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Use when you need to resolve an in-progress git merge/rebase conflict." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_resolving_merge_conflicts.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Resolve each hunk. Preserve both intents where possible. Where incompatible, pick the one matching the merge's stated goal and note the trade-off. Do not invent new behaviour. Always resolve; never --abort." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Discover the project's automated checks and run them — typically typecheck, then tests, then format. Fix anything the merge broke." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Find the primary sources for each conflict. Understand deeply why each change was made, and what the original intent was. Read the commit messages, check the PRs, check original issues/tickets." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Finish the merge/rebase. Stage everything and commit. If rebasing, continue the rebase process until all commits are rebased." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "See the current state of the merge/rebase. Check git history, and the conflicting files." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.resolving_merge_conflicts> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: tdd\nSource path: skills/engineering/tdd/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: tdd" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Test-driven development. Use when the user wants to build features or fix bugs test-first, mentions \"red-green-refactor\", or wants integration tests." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Use TDD when writing a regression test through public interfaces, confirming seams under test, or working red-green-refactor." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_tdd.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "A seam is the public boundary you test at: the interface where you observe behavior without reaching inside. Tests live at seams, never against internals." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Horizontal slicing — writing all tests first, then all implementation. Bulk tests verify imagined behavior: you test the shape of things rather than user-facing behavior, the tests go insensitive to real changes, and you commit to test structure before underst" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Implementation-coupled — mocks internal collaborators, tests private methods, or verifies through a side channel (querying the database instead of using the interface). The tell: the test breaks when you refactor but behavior hasn't changed." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Red before green. Write the failing test first, then only enough code to pass it. Don't anticipate future tests or add speculative features." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Tautological — the assertion recomputes the expected value the way the code does (expect(add(a, b)).toBe(a + b), a snapshot derived by hand the same way, a constant asserted equal to itself), so it passes by construction and can never disagree with the code. E" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Tests verify behavior through public interfaces, not implementation details. Code can change entirely; tests shouldn't. A good test reads like a specification — \"user can checkout with valid cart\" tells you exactly what capability exists — and survives refacto" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Ask: \"What's the public interface, and which seams should we test?\"" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Horizontal slicing — writing all tests first, then all implementation. Bulk tests verify imagined behavior: you test the shape of things rather than user-facing behavior, the tests go insensitive to real changes, and you commit to test structure before underst" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Implementation-coupled — mocks internal collaborators, tests private methods, or verifies through a side channel (querying the database instead of using the interface). The tell: the test breaks when you refactor but behavior hasn't changed." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "One slice at a time. One seam, one test, one minimal implementation per cycle." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Refactoring is not part of the loop. It belongs to the review stage (see the code-review skill), not the red → green implementation cycle." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "TDD is the red → green loop. This skill is the reference that makes that loop produce tests worth keeping: what a good test is, where tests go, the anti-patterns, and the rules of the loop. Every section applies on every cycle — consult them before and during" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Test only at pre-agreed seams. Before writing any test, write down the seams under test and confirm them with the user. No test is written at an unconfirmed seam. You can't test everything — agreeing the seams up front is how testing effort lands on the critic" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Tests verify behavior through public interfaces, not implementation details. Code can change entirely; tests shouldn't. A good test reads like a specification — \"user can checkout with valid cart\" tells you exactly what capability exists — and survives refacto" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "When exploring the codebase, read CONTEXT.md (if it exists) so test names and interface vocabulary match the project's domain language, and respect ADRs in the area you're touching." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.tdd> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: to-spec\nSource path: skills/engineering/to-spec/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: to-spec" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Turn the current conversation into a spec and publish it to the project issue tracker — no interview, just synthesis of what you've already discussed." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_to_spec.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "A description of what makes a good test (only test external behavior, not implementation details)" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Do NOT include specific file paths or code snippets. They may end up being outdated very quickly." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "This skill takes the current conversation context and codebase understanding and produces a spec (you may know this document as a PRD). Do NOT interview the user — just synthesize what you already know." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "A LONG, numbered list of user stories. Each user story should be in the format of:" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Architectural decisions" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "As a mobile bank customer, I want to see balance on my accounts, so that I can make better informed decisions about my spending" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "As an <actor>, I want a <feature>, so that <benefit>" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Explore the repo to understand the current state of the codebase, if you haven't already. Use the project's domain glossary vocabulary throughout the spec, and respect any ADRs in the area you're touching." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Sketch out the seams at which you're going to test the feature. Existing seams should be preferred to new ones. Use the highest seam possible. If new seams are needed, propose them at the highest point you can. The fewer seams across the codebase, the better -" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Technical clarifications from the developer" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "The interfaces of those modules that will be modified" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "The issue tracker and triage label vocabulary should have been provided to you — run /setup-matt-pocock-skills if not." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "The modules that will be built/modified" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "This list of user stories should be extremely extensive and cover all aspects of the feature." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Write the spec using the template below, then publish it to the project issue tracker. Apply the ready-for-agent triage label - no need for additional triage." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_spec> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: to-tickets\nSource path: skills/engineering/to-tickets/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: to-tickets" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Break a plan, spec, or the current conversation into a set of tracer-bullet tickets, each declaring its blocking edges, published to the configured tracker — edges as text in a local file, or native blocking links on a real tracker." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_to_tickets.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Do NOT close or modify any parent issue." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "A completed slice is demoable or verifiable on its own" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Any prefactoring should be done first" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Blocked by: which other tickets (if any) must complete first" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Does the granularity feel right? (too coarse / too fine)" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Each slice cuts a narrow but COMPLETE path through every layer (schema, API, UI, tests) — vertical, NOT a horizontal slice of one layer" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Each slice is sized to fit in a single fresh context window" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Give each ticket its blocking edges — the other tickets that must complete before it can start. A ticket with no blockers can start immediately." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "If you have not already explored the codebase, do so to understand the current state of the code. Ticket titles and descriptions should use the project's domain glossary vocabulary, and respect ADRs in the area you're touching." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "The issue tracker and triage label vocabulary should have been provided to you — run /setup-matt-pocock-skills if not." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Title: short descriptive name" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "What it delivers: the end-to-end behaviour this ticket makes work" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Work from whatever is already in the conversation context. If the user passes a reference (a spec path, an issue number or URL) as an argument, fetch it and read its full body and comments." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.to_tickets> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: triage\nSource path: skills/engineering/triage/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: triage" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Move issues and external PRs through a state machine of triage roles — categorise, verify, grill if needed, and write agent-ready briefs." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_triage.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Already implemented — the change already exists in the codebase. Point to where it lives; do not write to .out-of-scope/ (that KB is for *rejected* requests, not built ones)." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Gather context. Read the full issue or PR (body, comments, labels, author, dates; for a PR, the diff too). Parse any prior triage notes so you don't re-ask resolved questions. Explore the codebase using the project's domain glossary, respecting ADRs in the are" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "If prior triage notes exist on the issue or PR, read them, check whether the reporter has answered any outstanding questions, and present an updated picture before continuing. Don't re-ask resolved questions." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Unlabeled — never triaged." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "AGENT-BRIEF.md — how to write durable agent briefs" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Every comment or issue posted to the issue tracker during triage must start with this disclaimer:" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Every triaged issue should carry exactly one category role and one state role. If state roles conflict, flag it and ask the maintainer before doing anything else." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "For a PR, the same states read against the attached code: ready-for-agent means a brief is attached and an agent should take the next step on the diff; ready-for-human means it's ready for a human to merge." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "OUT-OF-SCOPE.md — how the .out-of-scope/ knowledge base works" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "bug — something is broken" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "enhancement — new feature or improvement" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "needs-info — waiting on reporter for more information" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "needs-triage — maintainer needs to evaluate" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "ready-for-agent — fully specified, ready for an AFK agent" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "ready-for-human — needs human implementation" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "wontfix — will not be actioned" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.triage> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#ImplementationPattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Imported from an external agent skill as a reviewable candidate.\nThis candidate is procedural guidance, not live authority.\nIt must be reviewed before promotion.\nSource skill: wayfinder\nSource path: skills/engineering/wayfinder/SKILL.md\nHuman review: promoted into the active AWG corpus as procedural engineering guidance.\nOriginal external skill pack: /home/dave/Documents/skills-main." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Skill: wayfinder" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#activationTrigger> "Plan a huge chunk of work — more than one agent session can hold — as a shared map of investigation tickets on your issue tracker, and resolve them one at a time until the way to the destination is clear." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#assertionMethod> "reviewed" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/architecture/patterns/ip_imported_skill_engineering_wayfinder.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "<!-- see \"Out of scope\": work ruled beyond the destination; closed, never graduates -->" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Every map and ticket is an issue, so it has a name — its title. In everything the human reads — narration, the map's Decisions-so-far — refer to it by that name, never by a bare id, number, or slug. A wall of #42, #43, #44 is illegible; names read at a glance." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Every ticket is either HITL — human in the loop, worked *with* a human who speaks for themselves — or AFK, driven by the agent alone. A HITL ticket only resolves through that live exchange; the agent never stands in for the human's side of it (a grilling agent" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Not yet specified when you can't yet phrase it that sharply. Don't pre-slice the fog into ticket-sized pieces: it's coarser than a ticket, and one patch may graduate into several tickets, or none, once the frontier reaches it." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Out-of-scope work never graduates — the frontier stops at the destination — so it returns only if the destination is redrawn, and then as a fresh effort, not a resumption." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Stop — charting the map is one session's work; do not also resolve tickets." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "The map is an index, not a store. It lists the decisions made and points at the tickets that hold their detail; a decision lives in exactly one place — its ticket — so the map never restates it, only gists it and links." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "The map is deliberately incomplete: don't chart what you can't yet see. Beyond the live tickets lies the fog of war — the dim view of decisions and investigations you can tell are coming but can't yet pin down, because they hang on questions still open. Resolv" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#forbiddenShortcut> "Two modes. Either way, never resolve more than one ticket per session." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "<closed ticket title> — <one-line gist of the answer>" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "<domain; skills every session should consult; standing preferences for this effort>" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "<what reaching the end of this map looks like — the spec, decision, or change this effort is finding its way to. One or two lines; every session orients to it before choosing a ticket.>" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "A session claims a ticket by assigning it to the dev driving the map, first, before any work, so concurrent sessions skip it. That assignee is the claim: an open, unassigned ticket is unclaimed." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Grilling (HITL): Conversation via the /grilling and /domain-modeling skills, one question at a time. The default case." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Prototype (HITL): Raise the fidelity of the discussion by making a cheap, rough, concrete artifact to react to — an outline, a rough take, a stub, or UI/logic code via the /prototype skill. Links the prototype as an asset. Use when \"how should it look\" or \"how" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Research (AFK): Reading documentation, third-party APIs, or local resources like knowledge bases. Creates a markdown summary as a linked asset. Use when knowledge outside the current working directory is required." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Task (HITL or AFK): Manual work that must happen before a *decision* can be made — nothing to decide, prototype, or research, but the discussion is blocked until it's done. Signing up for a service so its API can be judged, provisioning access, moving data so" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "The destination varies per effort, and naming it is the first act of charting — it shapes every ticket. It might be a spec to hand off and iterate on, a decision to lock before planning starts, or a change made in place like a data-structure migration. The map" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Ticket when the question is already sharp — even if it's blocked and you can't act on it yet." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Wayfinder is planning by default: each ticket resolves a decision, and the map is done when the way is clear — nothing left to decide before someone goes and does the thing. The pull to just do the work is usually the signal you've reached the edge of the map" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#mustFollow> "Where the map, its child tickets, blocking, and frontier queries physically live is tracker-specific. The issue tracker should have been provided to you — run /setup-matt-pocock-skills if not. Consult the tracker doc's \"Wayfinding operations\" section for how t" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#referenceFile> "ingestion_policy:docs/skill-ingestion.md" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#implementationPattern/imported.skill.engineering.wayfinder> <https://globular.io/awareness#status> "active" .
