<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.bootstrap_then_promote> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Bootstrap state is temporary scaffolding. It must be validated and promoted into authoritative desired state before it is treated as convergence truth. Search for bootstrap marker, promotion workflow, seed state, authoritative field." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.bootstrap_then_promote> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Bootstrap Then Promote" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.bootstrap_then_promote> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.bounded_critical_query> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.bounded_critical_query> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Queries in critical control paths must be bounded by context deadline, timeout, pagination, or safe fallback so they cannot block convergence indefinitely. Search for withBounded, context.WithTimeout, deadline, Query limit, pagination, bounded scan." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.bounded_critical_query> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Bounded Critical Query" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.bounded_critical_query> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.bulkhead> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.bulkhead> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Failure in one subsystem must not consume all shared control-plane capacity or starve unrelated work. Search for singleflight, per-service semaphore, lane, reconcile_slot, bounded concurrency, restart storm." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.bulkhead> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Bulkhead / Failure Isolation" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.bulkhead> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.circuit_breaker_distributed> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.circuit_breaker_distributed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "When a dependency is unhealthy, the system must stop amplifying the failure. It should fail fast, enter BLOCKED or DEGRADED state, or probe safely before resuming. Search for openCircuitBreaker, halfOpen, backoff, singleflight, DEGRADED, backend_health_gate." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.circuit_breaker_distributed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Circuit Breaker (Distributed Control Path)" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.circuit_breaker_distributed> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.consensus_backed_authority> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.consensus_backed_authority> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Critical cluster intent must be stored in a consensus-backed authority, not inferred from local disk, local runtime, or partial observation. etcd is the sole consensus backend. Search for etcd key paths, DesiredService, objectstore topology, local disk scan." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.consensus_backed_authority> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Consensus-Backed Authority" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.consensus_backed_authority> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.control_plane_data_plane> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.control_plane_data_plane> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A control plane decides and publishes authoritative intent; a data plane executes or serves runtime traffic. Runtime observation from the data plane must not become desired-state authority. Search for heartbeat, InfrastructureRelease, DesiredService, xDS, data-plane discovery." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.control_plane_data_plane> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Control Plane / Data Plane Boundary" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.control_plane_data_plane> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.desired_state_reconciliation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.desired_state_reconciliation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A reconciler compares authoritative desired state with installed/runtime state and moves toward convergence through explicit, bounded, and proven transitions. The three layers — desired, installed, runtime — are always distinct. Search for ComputeInfrastructureDesiredHash, CONVERGED, atomic_commit, installed_state, reconcile tick." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.desired_state_reconciliation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Desired State Reconciliation" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.desired_state_reconciliation> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.destructive_absence> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.destructive_absence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Missing, timed-out, or invalid control-plane state is interpreted as a stop or delete command." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.destructive_absence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Destructive Absence" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.destructive_absence> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.dns_independent_recovery> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.dns_independent_recovery> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Recovery paths must not depend only on DNS or service discovery when DNS or service discovery may be part of the failure. Provide direct endpoint, cached endpoint, or bootstrap authority fallback. Search for recovery.must_not_depend_on_dns_only, bootstrap endpoint, IP fallback, direct dial." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.dns_independent_recovery> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "DNS-Independent Recovery" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.dns_independent_recovery> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.durable_event_outbox> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.durable_event_outbox> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "State changes and event publication must not split into inconsistent partial truth. If event publication fails, state must remain recoverable or the event must be replayable. Search for audit record, event publish, workflow receipt, observation, notification." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.durable_event_outbox> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Durable Event / Outbox" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.durable_event_outbox> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.ephemeral_state_contamination> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.ephemeral_state_contamination> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Persistent storage from a previous cluster lifecycle carries stale node identities, profiles, or ownership records into a fresh boot. The new cluster silently inherits corrupted authority and diverges from the intended initial state." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.ephemeral_state_contamination> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Ephemeral State Contamination" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.ephemeral_state_contamination> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.error_swallowing> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.error_swallowing> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An error happens, but the code reports success or suppresses recovery." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.error_swallowing> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Error Swallowing" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.error_swallowing> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.explicit_degraded_mode> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.explicit_degraded_mode> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A distributed subsystem must expose whether it is FULL, DEGRADED, READ_ONLY, LOCAL_ONLY, BLOCKED, or UNAVAILABLE instead of failing ambiguously. Search for capability flags, degraded_reason, DEGRADED status, doctor finding, escalation." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.explicit_degraded_mode> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Explicit Degraded Mode" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.explicit_degraded_mode> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.fencing_token_generation_guard> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.fencing_token_generation_guard> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Writers must prove they still own the current leadership epoch, topology generation, or approval generation before committing authoritative state. Search for generation, compare-and-swap, approval_generation, topology_generation, epoch." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.fencing_token_generation_guard> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Fencing Token / Generation Guard" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.fencing_token_generation_guard> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.health_gate> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.health_gate> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Work must not be dispatched into a dependency unless that dependency is healthy enough for the class of work. Search for backend_health_gate, isHealthy, BLOCKED, DEGRADED, readiness, liveness." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.health_gate> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Health Gate" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.health_gate> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.idempotent_executor> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.idempotent_executor> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Executors must tolerate repeated instructions without corrupting state, duplicating side effects, or producing false success. Search for already-done guard, idempotent, checksum verify, singleflight, restart used as proof." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.idempotent_executor> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Idempotent Executor" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.idempotent_executor> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.intent_marker_tombstone> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.intent_marker_tombstone> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Deletion or destructive state transition must be represented by explicit intent, not inferred from missing state. Absence is unknown, not a command. Search for IsExplicitDisable, approval_marker, explicit_disabled, reason field, generation guard." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.intent_marker_tombstone> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Intent Marker / Tombstone" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.intent_marker_tombstone> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.last_known_good> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.last_known_good> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Critical consumers must preserve service continuity using the last validated good configuration when authority is temporarily unavailable. Never overwrite LKG with invalid or incomplete state. Search for LKG, last_known_good, holdConfig, ErrCompacted, Watch returns nil." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.last_known_good> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Last-Known-Good Runtime Continuity" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.last_known_good> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.leased_leadership_single_writer> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.leased_leadership_single_writer> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Only the current elected owner may write authoritative state. Leadership, ownership, and writer identity must be explicit and refreshed before committing critical state. Search for isLeader, leaderOnly, forwardToLeader, critical_state registry, owner field." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.leased_leadership_single_writer> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Leased Leadership / Single Writer" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.leased_leadership_single_writer> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.missing_intent_marker> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.missing_intent_marker> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A destructive action is performed without an explicit audited intent marker (approval token, generation, reason)." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.missing_intent_marker> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Missing Intent Marker" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.missing_intent_marker> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.partial_truth> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.partial_truth> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A richer identity or state exists, but control logic uses only part of it." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.partial_truth> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Partial Truth" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.partial_truth> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.persistence_gap> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.persistence_gap> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "State changes in memory but does not become durable. The persistent store is never updated." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.persistence_gap> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Persistence Gap" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.persistence_gap> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.read_repair_authority_repair> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.read_repair_authority_repair> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Authoritative owners must repair missing derived or published state from durable source when safe, rather than letting derived absence block recovery. Only the owner may repair — never infer authority from derived absence. Search for republish, repair, pki.ca_metadata, objectstore desired state, read_repair." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.read_repair_authority_repair> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Read Repair / Authority Repair" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.read_repair_authority_repair> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.runtime_observation_as_desired_authority> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.runtime_observation_as_desired_authority> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A component observes the running state and writes it back as the authoritative desired state, bypassing the controller's decision authority." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.runtime_observation_as_desired_authority> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Runtime Observation As Desired Authority" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.runtime_observation_as_desired_authority> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.saga_durable_workflow> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.saga_durable_workflow> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A multi-step operation must record durable progress and be resumable after crashes, leader changes, and partial failures. Search for step_receipts, pending_sync, workflow receipt, atomic_commit, executor_lease, idempotent step." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.saga_durable_workflow> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Saga / Durable Workflow" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.saga_durable_workflow> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.split_brain_prevention> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.split_brain_prevention> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Two actors or subsystems must not both believe they are the authoritative owner of the same critical state or topology. Search for single-owner registry, cluster_id, conflict resolution, last-write-wins, writer identity audit." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.split_brain_prevention> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Split-Brain Prevention" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.split_brain_prevention> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.stale_authority> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.stale_authority> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A component keeps using an old leader, endpoint, owner, or routing decision." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.stale_authority> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Stale Authority" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.stale_authority> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.unbounded_critical_query> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.unbounded_critical_query> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A query in a critical control path runs without a context deadline and can block indefinitely." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.unbounded_critical_query> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Unbounded Critical Query" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.unbounded_critical_query> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.unit_type_shadowing> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.unit_type_shadowing> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A systemd unit declares Type= more than once. The last declaration silently wins. Services that expect Type=simple but have a later Type=notify never leave activating state, blocking any unit with After= or Wants= on them." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.unit_type_shadowing> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Unit Type Shadowing" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.unit_type_shadowing> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.unverified_runtime_truth> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.unverified_runtime_truth> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Runtime observation is treated as desired authority without validation." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.unverified_runtime_truth> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Unverified Runtime Truth" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.unverified_runtime_truth> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.version_only_identity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#Pattern> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.version_only_identity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Control logic uses only the version string to identify an artifact or release, ignoring build_id, checksum, and platform." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.version_only_identity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Version-Only Identity" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#pattern/pattern.version_only_identity> <https://globular.io/awareness#authoredIn> "docs/awareness/generic/patterns.yaml" .
<https://globular.io/awareness#patternMisuse/pattern_misuse.cross_domain_leak> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://globular.io/awareness#PatternMisuse> .
<https://globular.io/awareness#patternMisuse/pattern_misuse.cross_domain_leak> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Foreign rules give an agent invalid architectural context and can block or misdirect edits in a repo they were never meant for." .
<https://globular.io/awareness#patternMisuse/pattern_misuse.cross_domain_leak> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Loading or applying knowledge without honouring the resolved scope, so a rule from one repo/domain leaks into another's briefing/query." .
